article.headline: Begley's 22 lead Quakers past cold Bobcats
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Tim Begley scored a game-high 22 points and Mark Zoller added 10 with 15 rebounds as Penn built a big lead and rolled to a 74-60 victory over Quinnipiac in the opening round of the Preseason NIT on Tuesday night. Steve Danley contributed 11 points for the Quakers (1-0), who advance to a game against Providence in the next round. The Friars squeezed past Niagara 83-78 and will host Penn on Thursday. The Quakers used a big run and took advantage of a dismal shooting performance by Quinnipiac (0-1) to open a 21-point halftime lead. Leading 10-8, Penn ran off 14 unanswered points to take control of the contest. Begley scored six and capped the run with a driving layup to give Penn a 24-8 advantage with 8:42 left in the opening half. The Bobcats went over 10 minutes without a field goal and Penn took advantage to build its lead to 34-12 on a basket by Zoller with 5:24 to play before halftime. Penn went to the locker room with a 43-22 cushion. The Bobcats fell out of contention by hitting just 23 percent of their shots in the half. Kevin Jolley led Quinnipiac with 12 points.
